<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="402" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[813,1452,813,1022]" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[813,930,813,837]" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[813,924,813,837]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">Diagnosis</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
– Total length 4.66-5.88; carapace with distinct pattern; epigynal plate of female with a pair of slightly concaved lateral hollows; pedipalp with several thick setae clustering together, median apophysis triangle shaped, directed laterally, distal part twisted in 90 and curved ventrally, distal margin truncated, embolus slightly twisted, distal part thin and long, terminal apophysis slightly curved.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="402" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[813,1452,1060,1114]" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[813,955,1060,1084]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">Etymology. –</emphasis>
The specific name refers to the truncated distal part of the median apophysis.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="403" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[813,1452,1153,1239]" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[813,1050,1153,1177]" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[813,962,1153,1177]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">Description. –</emphasis>
Female
</emphasis>
: 
<typeStatus box="[1062,1164,1153,1176]" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">Holotype</typeStatus>
: Total length 5.88, carapace length 3.13, width 2.27; abdomen length 2.88, width 1.96. Body brown. Head sloped laterally. Carapace with distinct
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4618995" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4618995" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4618995/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" startId="3.[113,158,2036,2057]" targetBox="[118,1446,1329,1973]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph blockId="3.[113,1452,2036,2114]" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">
Figs. 11-16. 
<taxonomicName authority="Tso &amp; Chen, 2004" authorityName="Tso &amp; Chen" authorityYear="2004" box="[235,412,2036,2057]" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Arcotosa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="truncata" status="new species">
<emphasis box="[235,412,2036,2057]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">Arcotosa truncata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[424,544,2036,2057]" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
. 11. carapace (female, dorsal view); 12-13. epigynum (12. ventral view; 13. dorsal view); 14- 15. left pedipalp of male (14. ventral view; 15. retrolateral view); 16. terminal part of right pedipalp (ventral view). Scale bars: Fig. 11 = 0.80mm; Figs. 12-15 = 0.15mm; Fig. 16 = 0.10mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,776,193,728]" pageId="4" pageNumber="403">
pattern (
<figureCitation box="[224,301,193,216]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="3.[113,158,2036,2057]" captionTargetBox="[118,1446,1329,1973]" captionTargetId="figure-520@3.[98,1459,1312,1989]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs. 11-16. Arcotosa truncata, new species. 11. carapace (female, dorsal view); 12-13. epigynum (12. ventral view; 13. dorsal view); 14- 15. left pedipalp of male (14. ventral view; 15. retrolateral view); 16. terminal part of right pedipalp (ventral view). Scale bars: Fig. 11 = 0.80mm; Figs. 12-15 = 0.15mm; Fig. 16 = 0.10mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4618995" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4618995/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="403">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
), median band extending anteriorly between PLEs; lateral bands broken; sublateral bands narrow; margins of carapace dark brown. Anterior eye row almost straight, AME slightly larger than ALE, AME-AME longer than AME-ALE. Clypeus about 0.9 times the diameter of AME. Chelicerae with 3 promarginal teeth and 3 retromarginal teeth. Sternum yellowish-brown, with brown spots along margins. Legs and pedipalp with distinct annulations. Leg measurements: I 7.35 (2.15, 0.98, 1.65, 1.59, 0.98); II 6.86 (1.96, 0.98, 1.41, 1.53, 0.98); III 6.62 (1.90, 0.92, 1.23, 1.65, 0.92); IV 9.93 (2.70, 1.23, 2.02, 2.76, 1.22). Dorsum of abdomen scattered with whitish pubescence, and with pale spots along and behind heart stripe; middle part of venter brown, lateral yellowish. Epigynal plate with a pair of slightly concaved lateral hollows (
<figureCitation box="[417,496,641,664]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="3.[113,158,2036,2057]" captionTargetBox="[118,1446,1329,1973]" captionTargetId="figure-520@3.[98,1459,1312,1989]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs. 11-16. Arcotosa truncata, new species. 11. carapace (female, dorsal view); 12-13. epigynum (12. ventral view; 13. dorsal view); 14- 15. left pedipalp of male (14. ventral view; 15. retrolateral view); 16. terminal part of right pedipalp (ventral view). Scale bars: Fig. 11 = 0.80mm; Figs. 12-15 = 0.15mm; Fig. 16 = 0.10mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4618995" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4618995/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="403">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
), copulatory openings not distinct, copulatory tube short, spermathecae expanded, round (
<figureCitation box="[144,224,705,728]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="3.[113,158,2036,2057]" captionTargetBox="[118,1446,1329,1973]" captionTargetId="figure-520@3.[98,1459,1312,1989]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs. 11-16. Arcotosa truncata, new species. 11. carapace (female, dorsal view); 12-13. epigynum (12. ventral view; 13. dorsal view); 14- 15. left pedipalp of male (14. ventral view; 15. retrolateral view); 16. terminal part of right pedipalp (ventral view). Scale bars: Fig. 11 = 0.80mm; Figs. 12-15 = 0.15mm; Fig. 16 = 0.10mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4618995" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4618995/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="403">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,776,768,952]" lastBlockId="4.[835,1474,193,344]" pageId="4" pageNumber="403">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,203,768,792]" pageId="4" pageNumber="403">Male:</emphasis>
Total length 4.66, carapace length 2.70, width 2.02; abdomen length 2.08, width 1.47. Similar to female in general shape and colour. Body slightly darker than female. Clypeus about 0.6 times the diameter of AME. Legs measurements: I 7.04 (1.96, 0.92, 1.59, 1.53, 1.04); II 6.44 (1.72, 0.86, 1.35, 1.47, 1.04); III 5.93 (1.65, 0.67, 1.16, 1.59, 0.86); IV 9.20 (2.33, 0.98, 1.96, 2.70, 1.23). Pedipalp with several thick setae clustering together. Median apophysis triangular, directed laterally, distal part twisted in 90 and curved ventrally, distal margin truncated (
<figureCitation box="[1042,1172,289,312]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="3.[113,158,2036,2057]" captionTargetBox="[118,1446,1329,1973]" captionTargetId="figure-520@3.[98,1459,1312,1989]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs. 11-16. Arcotosa truncata, new species. 11. carapace (female, dorsal view); 12-13. epigynum (12. ventral view; 13. dorsal view); 14- 15. left pedipalp of male (14. ventral view; 15. retrolateral view); 16. terminal part of right pedipalp (ventral view). Scale bars: Fig. 11 = 0.80mm; Figs. 12-15 = 0.15mm; Fig. 16 = 0.10mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4618995" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4618995/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="403">Figs. 14-15</figureCitation>
); embolus narrow, slightly twisted; terminal apophysis slightly curved (
<figureCitation box="[1319,1400,321,344]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="3.[113,158,2036,2057]" captionTargetBox="[118,1446,1329,1973]" captionTargetId="figure-520@3.[98,1459,1312,1989]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs. 11-16. Arcotosa truncata, new species. 11. carapace (female, dorsal view); 12-13. epigynum (12. ventral view; 13. dorsal view); 14- 15. left pedipalp of male (14. ventral view; 15. retrolateral view); 16. terminal part of right pedipalp (ventral view). Scale bars: Fig. 11 = 0.80mm; Figs. 12-15 = 0.15mm; Fig. 16 = 0.10mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4618995" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4618995/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="403">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="403" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[835,1474,385,632]" pageId="4" pageNumber="403">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[835,955,385,409]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="403">Remarks. –</emphasis>
This species is very close to 
<taxonomicName authority="Wang &amp; Qiu, 1992" authorityName="Wang &amp; Qiu" authorityYear="1992" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Arctosa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="403" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xunyangensis">
<emphasis box="[1248,1474,385,408]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="403">Arctosa xunyangensis</emphasis>
Wang &amp; Qiu, 1992
</taxonomicName>
. It can be distinguished from the latter by following: in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tso &amp; Chen" authorityYear="2004" box="[980,1101,449,472]" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Arcotosa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="403" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="truncata">
<emphasis box="[980,1101,449,472]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="403">A. truncata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, body smaller (female length 5.88, male length 4.66), copulatory opening not distinct, distal part of median apophysis truncated; in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wang &amp; Qiu" authorityYear="1992" box="[1225,1403,513,536]" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Arctosa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="403" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xunyangensis">
<emphasis box="[1225,1403,513,536]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="403">A. xunyangensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, body larger (female length 7.50-8.20, male length 5.20-5.70), copulatory opening distinct, distal part of median apophysis pointed and long.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
